# NestJS

Each module contains:
- `*.module.ts` — wiring
- `*.controller.ts` — HTTP layer only
- `*.service.ts` — business logic
- `*.repository.ts` — Prisma data access
- `dto/` — input validation classes
- `events/` — domain event handlers (when needed)
- `*.spec.ts` — unit tests

Response format: `{ data: T, message?: string }`.
Use `@CurrentUser()` decorator for authenticated user.
Register new modules in app.module.ts.
